-- Erste Group Falls First Day in Three on Moody’s Credit Downgrade
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-06-06T07:44:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/erste-group-falls-first-day-in-three-on-moody-s-credit-downgrade.html
Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  snapped two days
of gains after Moody’s Investors Service cut its credit rating
along with other Austrian lenders.  The shares fell 0.6 percent to 366.9 koruna by 9:36 a.m. in
Prague trading. Erste,  Austria ’s largest bank, had its long-term
debt  rating  cut two grades to A3, Moody’s said today in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
